the model is also modular we can easily\nintegrate arbitrarily complex physics of planetary light scattering. A\ncomparison against existing tools and analytical models of reflected light\nreveals that our model, despite its novel features, reliably reproduces light\ncurves under common circumstances. Pryngles source code is written in PYTHON\nand made publicly available.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Jul 2022 14:30:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 Jul 2022 16:11:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 6 Aug 2022 18:46:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-09"}
